The article announces the nomination of Jay Clayton to be the United States Attorney for the Southern District of New York for a four-year term. Clayton is currently the Chairman of the United States Securities and Exchange Commission and has served in various roles related to financial markets. Under his leadership, the SEC has taken enforcement actions and ordered parties to pay billions of dollars in disgorgement and penalties, with a significant amount returned to investors. Prior to his role at the SEC, Clayton was a partner at Sullivan & Cromwell LLP and also had teaching experience at the University of Pennsylvania Law School. He holds degrees in Engineering, Economics, and Law from prestigious institutions.